stylometry: In our group project we compared to machines from Wyatt printing. The one machine we looked at was a normal copier and the other one was a larger printing press. We wanted to find out at how many copies did we want to start using the other machine to minimize costs for the company. So we looked at the variable costs and fixed costs of each machine, also the outputs of each machine and ran those numbers based on an 8 hour work day. We then ran a sensitivity anaylsis which showed the break down of when to use each machine and where the cutoff points were to save the most money. From doing this project I learned that there are models on excel for close to anything you just need to figure out how to plug in the data in the right format to solve that probelm.
